BMW has invested in Parkmobile, a provider of mobile parking solutions in North America. The service helps people find and pay for parking on their mobile device. Through the transaction, Parkmobile has consolidated its shareholder base and gained access to capital. BMW, which was a minority investor in Parkmobile since 2014, will now be the sole outside investor after buying out the legacy shareholders in the business. BMW said its investment in Parkmobile will help to “drive continued expansion and innovation throughout North America”. Parkmobile achieved record revenue growth in 2017, thanks to processing over 50 million parking transactions. The company has also passed 8 million registered users and an inventory of over 1 million parking spots.